::Feline::

She pulled away from Chordate and smiled.  She tried to catch her 
breath.  She smiled and blushed. She whispered,"whoah.....I 
mean...ah..."  She looked at him and into his eyes. She shook her 
head to clear it and then looked around to make sure no one else saw 
them.  If someone had seen them, she would have to make a few changes 
in her plans, but nothing drastic.  She looked at him, she tried to 
speak, but no words came out.  She closed her mouth and giggled 
slightly as if embarressed a bit.   She stood up and held his hand, 
still blushing,"I was wondering, could we go for a walk? I think I 
need some air. Ah, Is it hot in here or is it just me?" She fanned 
her face with her other hand. Making it look like she was trying to 
cool down. Still holding his hand, " I'm very sorry,I don't normally 
do that with someone I just met. I mean I don't just and kiss total 
strangers like that. I mean..." she was acting flustered and 
nervouse.  "Oh, I'm sorry."  She looked at the doorway and saw no 
one. Coast clear, she thought. She looked at Chordate,"Uhm, how about 
that walk?"
